<p>I would like to see the vagueness of that wording cleaned up.</p>
<p>As well, my point is that feeding it is defeating the purpose of containment; if it will eat one child every X amount of time, and we FEED it one child every X amount of time, then we aren't actually containing it, since that is 90% of the danger of it. All we are doing it keeping it from migrating. We aren't doing anything at all to limit its harmful affect on humanity. I refuse to believe the Foundation was like &quot;eh, fuck it, just throw kids at it, that's easy.&quot; I would think at least some effort would be made at coming up with something a little more humane and less wasteful.</p>

