			<div class="content" id="post-content-1416200">
									

<p>I get what you're trying to do, Drew, but I'm still not buying it, I'm afraid. You've just added an arbitrary &quot;feed it the kid OR ELSE!&quot; to the scenario; it still feels faulty, given the killpower of the Foundation. Making its active puberty phase so much worse doesn't really follow naturally from the theme.</p>
<p>Does the mandatory-child-murder really help it? Even if the Foundation had to expose the child, then save the child, you've created a pretty terrifying situation with horrible aftereffects on the child's mental health.</p>

